05/01/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The EU should be more intensely involved in helping Balkan countries develop, European Commission President Romano Prodi said on Friday (3 January) in an interview with the Greek newspaper <I>To Vima</I>. 
He said the EU should not spare any efforts in supporting the security and progress of the region, and expressed hope that all Southeast European countries would receive an invitation to join EU as soon as possible. 
(Makfax, A1 TV - 04/01/03)
